$DNA Two terms I always see misused in investing are: 

Recency Bias
Reversion to the Mean

In my opinion, the last 1-2 years is recent. People are hijacking the last year of awful performance as an assured continuance of awfulness.

If you believe in Reversion to the Mean, because it’s a real thing, then bad performing stocks, “should” revert to the Mean if business is as good or getting better.  The Mean for DNA is somewhere around $5.50-$6 based on Volume. Not including Volume, someone could game the Stats and say it’s $7 or $4. Regardless, it’s higher. 

Again, people typically apply Recency Bias to Great times only get BETTER. The Bias is a warning that they will not get better. They revert to their Mean. 

The Recency Bias of Bears is that the bad stock action must and will get worse. 

Something to think about. miraeassetmf.co.in/knowledg...
